values: To sink into something is to slowly fall into it.
The boat had a hole in it, and it sank into the ocean.
n. 水槽；洗涤槽；污水坑 vi. 下沉；消沉；渗透 vt. 使下沉；挖掘；使低落

To sink is to descend below the surface of a liquid or to fall or drop downward.
Sink means to descend or fall downward, often into water or a hole.
